    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offered is a concours-level 2002 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2), a definitive example of the 3.6L flat-six era featuring VarioCam Plus timing. This vehicle is mechanically superlative, featuring a documented dual-row ceramic IMS bearing retrofit and a proactive rear main seal replacement. The G96 6-speed manual transaxle provides crisp, short-throw engagement, while the chassis retains its factory-fresh rigidity with refreshed Bilstein B6 dampers and Michelin Pilot Sport 4S tires. A recent DME report confirms zero overrevs in ranges 2 through 6, verifying the integrity of the rotating assembly. The cooling system has been optimized with a low-temperature thermostat and high-flow water pump to ensure thermal stability. This is a turn-key, collector-grade driver\u2019s car for the discerning purist.",
